allowUnreachableCode.extendedDescription:
With this option enabled, the following code snippet will not yield any compilation errors ```typescript
const fn = () => {
  if (true) {
    return 'reachable'
  } else {
    return 'also reachable'
  }
  return 'totally unreachable'
}
```

allowUnusedLabels.extendedDescription:
A perceptively unknown, or rarely used JavaScript feature is a labeled statement. It is used with `break` or `continue` statements in loop operations. The `allowUnusedLabels` flag enables TypeScript to not report errors when a label is unused such as in the following code snippet: ```typescript
loop: while(x < 10) {
  x++
}
```
